    "CommitMsg": "security: read OAuth token from URL fragment instead of query string\n\nThe backend now delivers the session JWT in the URL fragment\n(#token=...\u0026role=...). Parse it from location.hash (query ?token= still\naccepted for backward compatibility) and strip it from the visible URL.\nFragments are never sent to the server, logged, or leaked via Referer.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
    "Author": "rhinosys \u003cnicolas.rineau@rhinosys.fr\u003e",
    "Committer": "rhinosys \u003cnicolas.rineau@rhinosys.fr\u003e"
  },
